notes.note:
Good morning Will, thank you for reaching out to touch base about the on going repair to Bonnie's Explorer. That is unfortunate to hear. Fortunately, she is covered for the transmission replacement. Please note, the customer has a maximum single claim limit of $2500 less a $100 deductible for a total of $2400.00. I have added the remaining balance of this max claim as parts to the originally authorized parts and labour break down I provided earlier. 

The originally authorized of $998.51 goes towards the replacement of the valve body, and the remainder of the authorized amount can be used towards the replacement of the transmission with either the used option you provided, or the rebuild of the transmission as you suggested. We suggest that the customer go with the rebuild option, as opposed to installing a used transmission. Please make sure to advise the customer that if they choose to go with a used transmission to save themselves some money over and above the maximum claim limit, we will no longer provide warranty on that used transmission. The remainder of the contract will stay in tact, but there will be no on going coverage on the used transmission. Please make sure to let me know which option the customer would like to proceed with prior to performing the repair. The payout is as follows: 

Parts-$1964.95 (Original $630.20 for valve body + $1334.75 additional for transmission parts)
Labour-$390.00 (From original valve body replacement)
Deductible-$100.00
PST-27.30
Gst-$117.75
Authorization-CNU14BFUZ9

Total = $2400.00

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards, 

Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
